Chagas disease is caused by a protozoa
called [UNKNOWN].

38
00:02:24,531 --> 00:02:29,640
Trypanosomes in the feces of the reduviid
bug, can access through breaks in

39
00:02:29,640 --> 00:02:32,970
the skin from a person scratching the
intensely peridic bite.

40
00:02:35,215 --> 00:02:38,735
Microbes can also gain access to entry
portals by swimming or crawling.

41
00:02:38,735 --> 00:02:42,170
Free-living organisms, such as round
worms, use this strategy.

42
00:02:44,250 --> 00:02:47,610
Vectors gain access to hosts by using
sensing cues.

43
00:02:47,610 --> 00:02:50,430
Production of carbon dioxide is a common
strategy used by

44
00:02:50,430 --> 00:02:55,100
mosquitoes which can transmit Plasmodium,
the protozoa that causes malaria.

45
00:02:55,100 --> 00:02:59,670
And it's also used by ticks which can
transmit Borrelia burgdorferi,

46
00:02:59,670 --> 00:03:00,949
the bacteria that causes lyme disease.

47
00:03:01,990 --> 00:03:05,160
Vectors can also use temperature,
vibration, shadows, and

48
